The negro that drives the dray of the stone-yard —
steady and tall he stands, poised on one leg on
the string-piece;

His blue shirt exposes his ample neck and breast, and

     loosens over
								his hip-band;

His glance is calm and commanding — he tosses the

     slouch of his
